-- Romanian Protesters Clash With Riot Police, About 50 Injured
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-01-16T07:24:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-16/romanian-protesters-clash-with-riot-police-about-50-injured.html
About 50 people have been injured in
the Romanian capital Bucharest, following violent protests
during the weekend against austerity measures,  Mediafax 
reported, citing the national emergency service.  Some of the protesters, who have been identified as
supporters of three Bucharest-based football teams, clashed with
riot police, throwing stones, burning cars and breaking into
stores, police spokesman Florin Hulea was quoted as saying by
Realitatea TV.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
